ResourceHeader.ResourceName: MMS 4 Fast Plasma Investigation, Dual Ion Spectrometer (FPI, DIS) Distribution Moments, Burst Survey
ResourceHeader.Description: FPI usually operates in Fast Survey (FS) Mode in the MMS Region Of Interest (ROI) for the current Mission Phase. Data are taken at burst (30/150 ms for DES/DIS) resolution in this mode. Data are also made available at survey (4.5 s, etc) resolution. Per mission design, not all burst-resolution data are downlinked, but all survey data are downlinked. Planning around calibration activities, avoidance of Earth radiation belts, etc, when possible, FPI usually operates in Slow Survey (SS) Mode outside of ROI, and then only the 60 s resolution survey data are available. This product contains results from integrating the standard moments of phase-space distributions formed from the indicated data type (DES/DIS burst, FS or SS). For convenience, some additional parameters are included to augment those most commonly found in a moments product of this sort, plus time-stamps and other annotation characterizing the state of the instrument system at the indicated time.

Parameter.Name: Epoch Time
Parameter.Description: Epoch Time Tags in Terrestrial Time 2000 (TT2000)
Parameter.Caveats: MMS4 FPI/DIS burst data begin-time; derived from burst packet time. This parameter exhibits an increasing monotonic progression.

Parameter.Description: Epoch Plus Var
Parameter.Caveats: MMS4 FPI/DIS epoch plus var

Parameter.Name: Epoch Minus Var
Parameter.Description: Epoch Minus Var
Parameter.Caveats: MMS4 FPI/DIS epoch minus var

Parameter.Name: Data Quality Error Flags
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Description: Vector of Data Quality Indicators at Burst Start Time
Parameter.Caveats: Value of zero signifies no quality errors. For non-zero values: Bit-0 = manually flagged interval, Bit-1 = overcounting/saturation effects likely present in skymap, Bit-2 = reported spacecraft potential above 20V, Bit-3 = invalid/unavailable spacecraft potential, Bit-4 = significant (>25%) cold plasma (<10eV) component, Bit-5 = significant (>25%) hot plasma (>30keV) component, Bit-6 = high sonic Mach number (v/vth > 2.5), Bit-7 = low calculated density (n_DES < 0.05 cm^-3), Bit-8 = bentPipe magnetic field used instead of brst l2pre magnetic field, Bit-9 = srvy l2pre magnetic field used instead of brst l2pre magnetic field, Bit-10 = no internally generated photoelectron correction applied

Parameter.Name: Compression Flag
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Description: Compression Lossless/lossy Indicator at Survey Start Time
Parameter.Caveats: FPI/DIS compression loss indicator, 0=lossless, 1=lossy

Parameter.Name: Step Table Parity
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Description: Step Table Parity, this Burst
Parameter.Caveats: FPI/DIS alternates between two tables, designated even (0) and odd (1).

Parameter.Name: Start Del-Phi Spin Phase Count
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Description: Del-Phi (Observation Spin Phase) Count at Burst Start Time
Parameter.Caveats: Nominally, spin-phase counts range over [0000, 5759] cnts. Each count represents 1/16 deg of observatory spin-phase. Zero spin-phase count indicates obs +X-axis aligned with Sun.

Parameter.Name: Start Del-Phi Spin Phase Angle
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Description: Del-Phi (Observation Spin Phase) Angle at Burst Start Time
Parameter.Caveats: Nominally, spin-phase angles range over [0, 360) deg. Each count represents 1/16 deg of observatory spin-phase. Zero spin-phase angle indicates obs +X-axis aligned with Sun.

Parameter.Name: Sector Despin P Value
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Description: Sector Despin P Value, this Burst
Parameter.Caveats: Records P-value used to de-spin this burst sky-map on board. See FPI docs for details.

Parameter.Description: Ion Energy Spectrum "near" +X DSC during this Burst
Parameter.Caveats: Counts, summed over DSC velocity-dirs closest to +X_DSC, by energy bin.

Parameter.Name: Pitch Angle Indices
Parameter.Description: Pitch Bin Index used in some Types of Outputs
Parameter.Caveats: pitch-angle bins: pitch index=00 bins quasi-parallel to B, ..., pitch index=29 bins quasi-anti-parallel to B. pitch-angle bin size: 6 deg.

Parameter.Name: Energy Index
Parameter.Description: Energy Bin Index used in some Types of Outputs
Parameter.Caveats: FPI operations nominally bin data from 64 energy filters into 32 pairwise energy bins, indexed 0-31. Nominally, bins are indexed in increasing energy order. See FPI docs for details.
